<title type="html"><![CDATA[12/01(Thu) The first ever defendant found not guilty due to multiple personalities/Let's talk about our big family REC]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://www.royalclub.tw/bbs3/viewtopic.php?t=676&amp;p=704#p704"><![CDATA[
12/01(Thu) The first ever defendant found not guilty due to multiple personalities / Let's talk about our big family Royal English club.<br /><br />The first ever defendant found not guilty due to multiple personalities (Host: Zoe)<br /><br />Agenda:<br />7:00-7:10 pm Opening Remarks<br />7:05-7:40 pm Session 1: Group Discussion<br />7:40-8:00 pm Individual Presentation<br />8:00-8:05 pm Break<br />8:05-8:40 pm Session 2: Group Discussion<br />8:40-9:00 pm Individual Presentation<br /><br />We will hold a zoom meeting only.<br /><br />Zoom meeting: Please click the link below<br /><br /><!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="https://zoomtw.zoom.us/j/92987266213?pw">https://zoomtw.zoom.us/j/92987266213?pw</a><!-- m --> ...<br />Meeting ID:929 8726 6213<br />Password:112233<br /><br />--------------------------------------------<br /><br />Session 1: The first ever defendant found not guilty due to multiple personalities.<br /> *** Please note that multiple personality disorder does not automatically endangers society ,Billy’s case could be a rare one.<br /><!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="https://www.esquire.com/entertainment/tv/a37693537/billy-milligan-true-story-netflix-24-faces/">https://www.esquire.com/entertainment/t ... -24-faces/</a><!-- m --><br /><br />Questions<br />1.Do you believe Billy has multiple personality disorder or was he pretending in order to escape responsibility for crimes he committed?<br />2.If you were a judge would you find him guilty or innocent? What kind of punishment should he get? <br />3.People say most mental illnesses are due to Complex Trauma during childhood. What do you think?<br />4.What if your family ,neighbor or coworker has multiple personality disorder, what you gonna do?<br />5.Compared with the western world, this disease seems rare in our society. what do you think the reason is ?<br /><br />Session 2: <br /><br />Feel free to discuss about our big family Royal English Club.<br /><br />Questions:<br />These questions below are for your reference.<br />1.What is your motivation for learning English?<br />2.How long have you been a REC member and how did you know our REC?<br />3.Do you still remember your first meeting in the REC? How do you feel?<br />4.Do you have any interesting or regretful experiences in the REC to share with us?<br />5.Do you have any suggestion on how to improve our REC for the future?<br /><br /><br /><br />P.S.<br />1.參加三次(含實體及線上會議)後，只要繳交1,000元(學生500元)，即可成為ROYAL終身會員!<br />2.請帶著開放的心與熱情來參加全英文會話聚會!<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://www.royalclub.tw/bbs3/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=55735">zoe</a> — Thu Nov 24, 2022 10:17 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
